			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The &amp;quot;nsw&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;nuw&amp;quot; arithmetic attributes (&amp;quot;no signed wrap&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;no unsigned wrap&amp;quot;) don't appear to be used by the LLVM backend -- there's no references in lib/Codegen.  That's not surprising, because the hardware doesn't care if arithmetic overflows.  These attributes are there for the benefit of optimisation passes instead.

This means we can omit these attributes from the stable ABI.  This reduces the set of features we have to represent in a stable wire format.
